408
00:39:00,140 --> 00:39:06,820
therefore non-interfering state. And it turns out that if you filter now at 45 degrees this

409
00:39:06,820 --> 00:39:13,840
is the state function, the quantum wave function, that you end up with. You now have a photon

410
00:39:13,840 --> 00:39:19,450
that's either in the upper or lower slit and that's either horizontally or vertically polarized,

411
00:39:19,450 --> 00:39:24,540
and this kind of makes sense because if you think of these as vectors and you have a horizontal

412
00:39:24,540 --> 00:39:29,090
polarization plus a vertical polarization, that's a 45-degree polarization, which is

